    uptakeGuess

    uptakeGuess.Rd

    Function to help find good initial parameters by guessing the initial uptake using a generalised inverse appraoach

    uptakeGuess(res, numRep, numPeptides, numtimepoints, R, C, phi = 1)

    Arguments

    res

    An object of class DataFrame containing the results of the hdx-ms experiment

    numRep

    The number of replicates

    numPeptides

    The number of peptides

    numtimepoints

    The number of timepoints

    R

    The number of residues

    C

    A matrix indicating the position of the residues in the peptides.

    phi

    The maximum uptake possible. Default is 1.

    Value

    A matrix of intial uptake guesses

    Examples

    require(ReX)
require(dplyr)
data(BRD4_apo)

BRD4_apo <- BRD4_apo %>% filter(End < 100)
numTimepoints <- length(unique(BRD4_apo$Exposure))

            numRep = 3,
            numPeptides =  numPeptides,
            numtimepoints =  numTimepoints,
            R =  99,
            C = C,
            phi = 0.92)
